	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">oRBIT2002 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Being able to map PRGROM at $6000? </div><br />For FME-7 (Batman: Return of the Joker), right?<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Instead of mirroring, map "real" memory at $800-&gt; (where the main RAM is mirrored in normal case).</div><br />No. Without a modification to the NES itself, decoding any CPU address in $0000-$3FFF will cause a bus conflict. Otherwise, Game Paks would have already done it.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Being able to swap between CHRRAM and CHRROM in the same mapper?</div>
<br />For TQROM (Pinbot, High Speed) and its Chinese workalike, right?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
