	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Quick tutorial:
<br />
<br />-Download bunnyboy's CNROM example &amp; Xilinx ISE Webpack
<br />-File &gt; Open Project &gt; "cnrom.ise"
<br />-Process &gt; Implement top model
<br />-Double click "Generate Programming File"
<br />
<br />In the project folder if it compiled OK, there'll be a new .bit file. Take that and follow bunnyboy's instructions. You just need to insert it into the existing .map file and you're set. To make Powerpak recognize it, just rename it to the mapper you just created. Mapper 255 would be named "MAPFF.MAP"
<br />
<br />Obviously there's a lot more to using ISE, you really gotta play around to get the hang of everything and understand the program's quirks. Make sure you learn how to make "symbols" (encapsulate schematics), you'll need it as the worksheets are of fixed sizes.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


